# üêû bug report


### Is this a regression?

No


### Context

[perf_util.ts](https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/modules/e2e_util/perf_util.ts) defines the function `runBenchmark` which is a wrapper for benchpress's sampler. The function does three key things: 1. Open the browser to a given url, 2. Allow for some initial setup via a callback method "`setup`", and 3. Run a benchpress sampler to run `prepare` and `work` over and over again to get performance metrics.

This bug is specifically surrounding the `setup` callback, step 2 as described above.


### Description

Because we do not await `config.setup()` in [perf_util.ts L37](https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/modules/e2e_util/perf_util.ts#L37), if setup is an async function (which is very likely since setup code will probably be interacting with the dom) there is no guarantee the call to `config.setup()` will finish before the sampling begins.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Here is a simple test I wrote

```ts
  it('click (unchecked -> checked)', async() => {
    await runBenchmark({
      id: 'checkbox-overview-click-unchecked-to-checked',
      url: '',
      ignoreBrowserSynchronization: true,
      params: [],
      setup: async () => {
        await $('#show').click();
        console.log('setup before');
        await $('mat-checkbox').click();
        console.log('setup after');
      },
      prepare: async () => {
        console.log('prepare before');
        await $('mat-checkbox').click();
        console.log('prepare after');
      },
      work: async () => {
        console.log('execute before');
        await $('mat-checkbox').click();
        console.log('execute after');
      },
    });
  });
```

